  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 9.c, we use 60 DPUs and 16 vCPUs with different input file sizes.",
    "Fig. 9.a indicates that the execution time is independent of the number of vCPUs.",
    "In Fig. 9.b, we see that the execution time increases when the VM uses more DPUs, owing to the additional data transfer cost, even though all DPUs are executing in parallel.",
    "Fig. 9.c shows that in vPIM, the overhead decreases as the data size increases, ranging from 2.33× for 8MB to 1.29× for 60MB.",
    "This trend is attributed to the fixed time spent on message passing between the VM and Firecracker: as data transfer operations become lengthier, the proportion of time dedicated to message passing diminishes, thereby reducing the relative overhead."
  ],
